Team


Ben Schick
Ben Schick is the Founder and President of Cobalt Capital, Inc., the managing broker-dealer for Epoch Properties, Inc., since 2005. His main role is to coordinate relations and marketing between the selling group broker-dealers and the sponsor.
In 2000, he was a Construction Superintendent Assistant with Epoch Properties, Inc. From 2001-2004, Mr. Schick was a portfolio manager for Epoch Management, Inc. He was responsible for communication and budget analysis between the on site management and ownership.
Ben earned his B.S. degree from Humboldt State University in 1994. From 1995-2000 he was an instructor for the National Outdoor Leadership School, spending time in Baja California, Mexico and Alaska. He is also an avid surfer and trans-oceanic sailor.
– Holds Series 22, 39 and 63 securities licenses. 
– Licensed Florida Real Estate Broker.
 
Mariely Acosta
Mariely Acosta has been with Cobalt since its inception in 2005 and is currently the Chief Compliance Officer. She has helped develop operational, compliance procedures and protocols for the firm. She is responsible for the day-to-day operations of the office, including processing of incoming Subscription Documents. In addition, Mrs. Acosta is the main contact for clients and Registered Representatives.
-Mariely earned a B.S. degree from The Pennsylvania State University in 2004.
-She holds Series 22 and 39 securities licenses, as well as a Florida 2-15 Life, Health and Variable Annuities license.
 
Ashley Dixon
Ashley Dixon joined Cobalt Capital in 2013 and provides administrative support for the office. She assists with travel arrangements, presentations, client dinners and processing investment confirmations. 

-In her spare time she enjoys spending time with her family, reading and hiking.


















